args:
(I ain't no stranger to lost causes. Hell,
I fought my way through battles I had no
business survivin' more times than I know.
But this...)
Sorry I'm late!\nHave you been waiting long?
No problem, Helena. Only just got here.
(For the first time in my life, I got no\nidea how to proceed. Am I even gonna\nmake it through this...?)
My blade strikes as swift as the wind;\nconfusion will be the last thing you know!
Your skills are as impressive as ever.\nWe're truly blessed that you came all\nthe way from Hinomoto to aid us.
You honor me with your words, Princeâ€”\nbut don't be lowerin' your guard just yet.
Uh, HELLO? I'm here too, you know!\nDid you forget about me already?!
Well, hell. Looks like I did.\nEr, but what are you doin' here, anyway?
What do you think I'm doing?!
I came to Alberia to train,\nand I'm itching for combat!
*pant* *pant* Geez, give the rest of us\na chance to catch up!
If you're here to train, might wanna\nstart with those little stick legs.
You sure you're okay, ma'am?\nSay somethin' if you are.
R-right! I'm okay! Oh, and thank you\never so much for saving me.
My name is Helena. What's yours?
Addis is the handle. Now c'mon\nand let me see you home.
Thank you very much, Mr. Addis.\nEr, but I have to tell you something...
I am COMPLETELY in love with you\nand would do anything for us to\ngo out on a date together!
Love at first sight is a real thing?\nWell, I never.
Since the moment I first laid eyes on him,\nmy heart has been pounding so fiercely\nthat I can scarce draw breath!
I've heard the bards sing of this feeling,\nand know that it can only be love!
Look, you seem like a real nice gal,\nbut I'm afraid I don't feel the same.
Maybe the fact he's known you\nfor less than five minutes...?
Sure, there's that. But more importantly,\nI'm sworn to the service of Hinomoto.
I ain't about to forsake my loyalty to my\nlord by takin' a wife, and I'm not the type\nto lead a lady on if nothin' can come of it.
I'm not asking you to marry me.\nMy only request is a single date.
Give me that, and I swear to vanish from\nyour life as quickly as I arrived in it.
...Wait, and he AGREED? Holy smokes!\nSo when is this mystery date, mmm?
Ohmigosh, this is SO exciting! Love at first\nsight is such a rare and wonderful thing.
But she is one brave lady to stake\neverything on a single date like this.
And speak of the devil! The man himself!\n...Wait, you're not SERIOUSLY going out\ndressed like that, are you?
I can't believe I have to explain this,\nbut you're going out on a DATE.\nDates are supposed to be SPECIAL.
Are you even taking this seriously?
So what do you two jokers think I\nshould wear, eh? Somethin' with\na buncha buttons, probably...
Hee hee! Just leave eeeverything to us.
...And voila! Your makeover is complete.\nHer heart is gonna tear clean out of her\nchest when she sees the new you!
Honestly, Addis. Why do you even have\nthese other clothes if you never wear 'em?
I wasn't aware you COULD wear a kimono\nlike this. ...Feels kinda weird.
Yeah, but it doesn't LOOK weird, so relax.\nHeck, if anything, it's a big improvement.
Now good luck on your big date!
(...That's how I ended up in this mess.\nIs there even a clean way outta this,\nor am I in more trouble than I thought?)
(Gotta remember what Botan told meâ€”\nit'll be a serious slap in the face to Helena\nif I don't take this seriously.)
(So I'll just do everything in my power\nto give her the date of her dreams!)
